alwaysApply: true
---

1. Versioning & API Standards
Target: Unity 6 LTS / Entities 6.4.0.

Modern Syntax: Use ISystem (struct-based) and IJobEntity (Source Generator style). Always mark Systems and Jobs with [BurstCompile].

2. Movement & Transforms (No Physics)
LocalTransform Based: Do not use Rigidbody, PhysicsBody, or CapsuleCollider.

Direct Updates: Update LocalTransform components directly within Systems.

Interpolation: Use SystemAPI.Time.DeltaTime to ensure smooth, frame-rate independent movement for iOS (Metal).

3. Navigation (NavMeshQuery)
Thread-Safe Pathfinding: Use the NavMeshQuery API within IJobEntity.

Spatial Analysis: For NPC logic (like "Is my target still on a valid walk area?"), use NavMeshQuery.BeginLocation and NavMeshQuery.Raycast within jobs to avoid main-thread bottlenecks.

Avoid: Do not use UnityEngine.AI.NavMesh (the managed API) inside Jobs.

4. Rendering (Entities Graphics)
GPU-Driven: Use Entities Graphics for all NPC rendering to leverage GPU instancing and efficient culling.

Animations: Implement animations using Skinned Mesh Entities (GPU Skinning).

Baking: Ensure all NPCs use RenderMesh and MaterialMeshInfo components generated during the baking process via IBaker.

5. Data Structure (Components)
Blittable Structs: Only use IComponentData.

Tag Components: Use empty structs (e.g., struct NPCTag : IComponentData {}) for efficient query filtering.

Buffers: Use DynamicBuffer<T> for lists of data (like a path of waypoints) instead of NativeList inside components.

6. The Baking Pattern
Auto-Generation: When I request a new NPC feature, generate both the IComponentData and the corresponding IBaker<TAuthoring> in the same file.

Clean Mapping: Map Vector3 to float3 and Quaternion to quaternion automatically.
